# Vitest + tsdown Profiles

Apply one of two profiles and keep each package consistent:

- **Node/Core packages** (`cli`, `di`, `tailwind-variants` style)
  - Vitest: `environment: "node"`, `include: ["tests/**/*.test.?(c|m)[jt]s?(x)"]`, `passWithNoTests: true` (so `pnpm run verify` does not fail when the test tree is temporarily empty)
  - Coverage include: `src/**/*.ts`
  - Coverage exclude: `src/**/*.{test,bench}.?(c|m)[jt]s?(x)` and `**/*.d.ts`
  - tsdown exclude: `!src/**/*.{test,bench}.{ts,tsx}`

- **React/UI packages** (`ui`, `theme` style)
  - Vitest: `environment: "jsdom"`, `include: ["tests/**/*.test.?(c|m)[jt]s?(x)"]`, `passWithNoTests: true` (same reason as Node profile)
  - Coverage include: `src/**/*.{ts,tsx}`
  - Coverage exclude: `src/**/*.{test,stories}.?(c|m)[jt]s?(x)` and `**/*.d.ts`
  - tsdown exclude: `!src/**/*.{test,bench,stories}.{ts,tsx}`

## Consistency checks

- Keep config patterns aligned across packages of the same profile.
- Avoid one-off glob variants unless there is a documented package-specific reason.

## Profile selection for new packages

- Use **React/UI profile** when package tests run in `jsdom` or package has React UI surface.
- Use **Node/Core profile** otherwise (Node runtime libraries, CLIs, infrastructure/core packages).
